text: Nebria complanata is a species of ground beetle native to West and South Europe.Fauna EuropaeaCarl H. Lindroth 1974 Coleoptera. Carabidae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects Vol 4 Part 2. Royal Entomological Society,London pdf It is a coastal species predatory on Talitrus saltator and Talorchestia brito. ==References== complanata Category:Beetles described in 1767 Category:Taxa named by Carl Linnaeus Category:Beetles of Europe
title: Nebria complanata
